Dia. 01 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's \cf1\b placement \cf0\b0 at 1 is the \cf1\b vital point\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par It is not only at the 1-2 point but it is also looking at the snapback at A.
\par
\par Black 2 is the strongest way to resist, but White 3 is the deciding move.
\par
\par It doesn't help Black even if he connects with the next move at A.
\par }
